Its not very significant, browser fingerprinting is just a websites ability look at things like your screen resolution and certain preferences etc. It can be used to identify specific users in relation to other posts, so with your browser fingerprint, if you were posting from multiple ips, I might be able to associate them through your posts, but as long as youre never using your actual ip it cant actually be linked to you as a person. It also matters not at all if your browser isnt unique in any way, so if you use tor and leave tor in the defaul settings, the browser fingerprint means nothing at all. Its just an extra layer of redundant security in that case. Theres a thread on /tech/ woth instructions on modifying the 08chan conde from your computer to fix the issues in a better way if it really matters to you.

then you can start by hardening your usual browser with a script blocker like noscript or umatrix alongside the adblocker and other things like a cookie manager. Look up a guide on something like this. if everything is configured nicely, you dont really need to worry about using tor alongside your vpn as long as you trust you vpn. In addition to hiding yout ip in the tor netword, tor protects your identity from websites by making it difficult for websites to identify you based on your browser configuration, active logins, etc, but you can configure a regular browser to do all of this as well. Tor is a crutch like training wheels, its not some unique magic anonymizer, its just anonymity made easy.
